    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CHASSIS ACCESSORIES - DESCRIPTION - TRAILER CONNECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>TRAILER CONNECTION</title>
        <para>The 7-Way Trailer Socket (112) connects the tractor and trailer wiring for operation of Stop, Tail, Turn
            and Hazard signal lights and Tail and Clearance lights. Additionally, the trailer socket includes a circuit
            that provides voltage from the A1 accessory feed stud. The trailer socket terminals are color coded as shown
            in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0806001">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0806001" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0806001" filename="../figg08/G0806001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>TRAILER SOCKET (112)</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
